<subSubSection lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="6.[151,1437,1722,2019]" lastBlockId="7.[151,1437,152,371]" lastPageId="7" lastPageNumber="8" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">
This rhynchonellide species has a very complex taxonomic history. 
<bibRefCitation author="In" box="[998,1097,1722,1748]" pageId="6" pageNumber="30" refString="Atkins, D. (1959) A new species of Platidia (Brachiopoda) from the La Chapelle Bank Region. Journal of the Marine Biology Association of the United Kingdom, 38, 133 - 142." type="journal article" year="1959">
In 
<number box="[1032,1097,1722,1748]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1959.0">1959</number>
</bibRefCitation>
, G. A. Cooper assigned the present-day species 
<taxonomicName authority="Woodward, 1855" authorityName="Woodward" authorityYear="1855" box="[390,833,1761,1787]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[390,622,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Rhynchonella grayi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Woodward" box="[630,833,1761,1787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="33" refString="Woodward, S. P. (1855) Description of a new species of Recent Rhynchonella. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, series 2, 16, 444." type="journal article" year="1855">
Woodward, 
<number box="[774,833,1761,1787]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1855.0">1855</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
to the fossil genus 
<taxonomicName authority="Hertlein &amp; Grant, 1944" authorityName="Hertlein &amp; Grant" authorityYear="1944" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Eohemithiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1065,1217,1761,1786]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eohemithiris</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Hertlein" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Hertlein, L. G. &amp; Grant, U. S. (1944) The Cenozoic Brachiopoda of western North America. Publications of the University of California at Los Angeles in Mathematical and Physical Sciences, 3, 1 - 236." type="journal article" year="1944">
Hertlein &amp; Grant, 
<number box="[151,217,1800,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1944.0">1944</number>
</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
, known from the Eocene of California. Later, d’Hondt (
<number box="[932,998,1800,1826]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1987.0">1987</number>
) erected a new genus and species, 
<taxonomicName box="[151,352,1839,1864]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[151,352,1839,1864]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Basiliolella ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, for some material from off southern 
<collectingCountry box="[792,978,1838,1864]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
. Afterwards, based on the rich material collected around 
<collectingCountry box="[369,563,1877,1903]" name="New Caledonia" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">New Caledonia</collectingCountry>
and the Chesterfield Islands, 
<bibRefCitation author="Laurin" box="[944,1120,1877,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="31" refString="Laurin, B. (1997) Brachiopodes recoltes dans les eaux de la Nouvelle Caledonie et des iles Loyaute, Matthew et Chesterfield. In: Crosnier, A. (ed.), Resultats des Campagnes MUSORSTOM. Volume 18. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 176, 411 - 471." type="journal article" year="1997">
Laurin (
<number box="[1045,1110,1877,1903]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1997.0">1997</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
concluded that so-called 
<taxonomicName box="[151,380,1916,1941]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Eohemithiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[151,380,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eohemithiris grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[442,653,1916,1941]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[442,653,1916,1941]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Basiliolella ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are identical, and he synonymized both species under the name 
<taxonomicName box="[151,373,1954,1979]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Eohemithiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[151,373,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eohemithiris grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Further investigations (Savage 
<emphasis box="[757,809,1954,1979]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">et al</emphasis>
. 
<number box="[825,886,1954,1980]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="2002.0">2002</number>
) have shown that Cooper’s (
<number box="[1226,1287,1954,1980]" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" value="1959.0">1959</number>
) assignment of 
<taxonomicName box="[184,417,1993,2018]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[184,417,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Rhynchonella grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
to 
<taxonomicName box="[456,609,1993,2018]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Eohemithiris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="6" pageNumber="7" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[456,609,1993,2018]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="7">Eohemithiris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was incorrect and that this Recent species should be attributed to the genus 
<taxonomicName box="[228,365,152,177]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[228,365,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Basiliolella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
created by d’Hondt (
<number box="[622,687,152,178]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1987.0">1987</number>
). 
<collectingCountry box="[708,741,152,178]" name="American Samoa" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">As</collectingCountry>
<taxonomicName box="[749,846,152,177]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[749,846,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[905,999,152,177]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[905,999,152,177]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">B. ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are synonymous (confirmed also by my own examination of the material) the specific name 
<taxonomicName box="[806,868,191,216]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Rhynchonellidae" genus="Rhynchonella" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[806,868,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has priority over the name 
<taxonomicName box="[1190,1249,191,216]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="ferox">
<emphasis box="[1190,1249,191,216]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">ferox</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="8" type="reference_group">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,152,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
<taxonomicName box="[198,403,229,254]" class="Rhynchonellata" family="Basiliolidae" genus="Basiliolella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Rhynchonellida" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" phylum="Brachiopoda" rank="species" species="grayi">
<emphasis box="[198,403,229,254]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Basiliolella grayi</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was common in the present collections, being found on six seamounts and on the slope of the Isle of Pines (
<tableCitation box="[410,519,268,294]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[151,240,689,713]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparative species diversity on the seamounts as sampled by different cruises (Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2)" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Tables 
<number box="[503,519,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1.2">1</number>
</tableCitation>
, 2) at 
<quantity box="[603,745,268,294]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.725" metricValueMax="5.6" metricValueMin="1.85" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" unit="m" value="372.5" valueMax="560.0" valueMin="185.0">185–560 m</quantity>
(
<figureCitation box="[764,859,268,294]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="27.[151,255,1303,1327]" captionTargetBox="[151,1435,194,1278]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[151,1436,194,1279]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURE 14. Depth ranges of particular brachiopod species collected during the Norfolk 1 and Norfolk 2 cruises to the Norfolk Ridge, New Caledonia." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/190412/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">
Fig. 
<number box="[824,859,268,294]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="14.0">14</number>
</figureCitation>
). The species was also noted from off 
<collectingCountry box="[1352,1396,268,294]" name="Fiji" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fiji</collectingCountry>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Woodward" box="[151,365,306,332]" pageId="7" pageNumber="33" refString="Woodward, S. P. (1855) Description of a new species of Recent Rhynchonella. Annals and Magazine of Natural History, series 2, 16, 444." type="journal article" year="1855">
Woodward (
<number box="[295,356,306,332]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="1855.0">1855</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Logan" box="[422,583,306,332]" pageId="7" pageNumber="31" refString="Logan, A. (2007) Geographic distribution of extant articulated brachiopods. In: Selden, P. A. (ed.), Treatise on Invertebrate Paleontology. Part H. Brachiopoda Revised. Volume 6. Geological Society of America and University of Kansas, Boulder, Colorado and Lawrence, Kansas, pp. 3082 - 3115." type="book" year="2007">
Logan (
<number box="[513,575,306,332]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2007.0">2007</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
but was not found in the rich material from 
<collectingCountry box="[1107,1148,306,332]" name="Fiji" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Fiji</collectingCountry>
recently investigated by 
<bibRefCitation author="Bitner" box="[151,317,345,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="30" refString="Bitner, M. A. (2006 b) Recent Brachiopoda from the Fiji and Wallis and Futuna Islands, Southwest Pacific. In: Justine, J. L. &amp; Richer de Forges, B. (eds), Tropical Deep Sea Benthos. Volume 24. Memoires du Museum national d'Histoire naturelle, 193, 15 - 32." type="journal article" year="2006" yearSuffix="b">
Bitner (
<number box="[240,303,345,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2006.0">2006</number>
b
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<number box="[329,393,345,371]" pageId="7" pageNumber="8" value="2008.0">2008</number>
). It also occurs in the 
<collectingCountry box="[649,845,345,371]" name="Solomon Islands" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Solomon Islands</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry box="[902,998,345,371]" name="Vanuatu" pageId="7" pageNumber="8">Vanuatu</collectingCountry>
regions (Bitner in prep.).
</paragraph>
